article.headline: Georgia State 87, Towson 81, 2OT
article.story: ATLANTA (AP) -- Lance Perique scored 26 points and grabbed 14 rebounds and Rashad Chase added 23 points to lead Georgia State to an 87-81 win over Towson in double overtime on Saturday. The Panthers (5-8, 1-2 Colonial Athletic Association) rallied from a six-point deficit in the fourth quarter to tie the game at 64-64 with 11 seconds left on a 3-pointer by Chase, who also had 12 rebounds. Georgia State took a 72-69 lead in the first overtime. But Towson (6-7, 1-2) tied the game on Tim Crossin's free throw and a score from Gary Neal with 24 seconds left. Neal scored 30 points and had eight rebounds for Towson. Rocky Coleman added 21 points, seven rebounds and five assists. In the second overtime, Towson cut the lead to 80-79 with 1:57 remaining when Coleman made a basket from beyond the arc. But Georgia State pulled away when Chase hit two free throws then made a 3-pointer with 30 seconds left in the game. Panthers guard Leonard Mendez scored a career-high 19 points. Point guard Ron Larris grabbed 10 rebounds, had five assists and five points. Georgia State had a season-best 11 3-pointers.
